fields.description:
Opendream is a social-minded technologist led, digital natives, social enterprise based in Bangkok and Chiang Mai, Thailand devoted to creating usable and affordable technologies for social benefit organisations around the planet. We believe that the power of the Internet and communication technologies can change the world, and roll the wheel of society together to a challenge for the better future.

We drive by cutting edge technologies and passion, freedom and respect for people. With your power, together, we can help more people, sustainably.
fields.summary: Social-minded technologist led, digital natives, social enterprise.

fields.name: Playplanet
fields.description:
playplanet is a community of, by, and for people rocking on a journey.

This platform is a playground that everybody can share authentic experiences and local wisdom with others and create social impact.

playplanet connects travelers who are looking for authentic local experiences and locals who can provide it and encourage to make a better impact by traveling in better sustainable way.

How can we travel better for us and better for the earth?

playplanet starts its journey from the question, 'how we can make a social change through travel?' We find the answer in sustainable travel. When we travel with local people, we can see the world in the eye of local friends and it it is the best way of sustainable traveling which benefits local community, protects environment, and conserve local culture.

Connect. Inspire. Change.

playplanet believes that travel has a power to change one's life and the world by connecting people. Travel experience inspires people and these inspiration becomes seeds for personall innovation changing one's mind and behavior and leads social change to make the world better.

Life changing trip for everyone.
Let's play planet.

playplanet has awesome friends - like social enterprises and foundations and companies and creative and passionate individuals - over the world.

We aims to build global community for travelers who care for our planet earth by connecting people and providing better sustainable travel tool to make a difference on our journey.
fields.summary: Travel with locals Change the way you travel

fields.name: ChangeFusion
fields.description:
ChangeFusion is a Bangkok-based organization that grow social entrepreneurs for creative and sustainable change. We support and invest into social enterprises. We also facilitate a better ecosystems for them in Thailand and in Asia. Our portfolio social enterprises are working in various areas such as web & mobile tech, sustainable agriculture, sustainable tourism / community-based tourism, affordable healthcare, community-scale renewable energy, fair trade and more. 

ChangeFusion is a non-profit institute under the Thai Rural Reconstruction Movement Foundation under the Royal Patronage.

fields.description:
Travelers' MAP is a social enterprise provides fun and learning opportunity for the best experience to innovate social issues such as environmental problem like global warming and the gap between city/rural side, advanced/developed counties.

Originally it was a division in charge of tour within Haja Center that was created out of the need for an alternative education model to foster creativity and empathy amongst young people in Korea. At the beginning, the tour programs were focused on youth education and culture. Travelers' Map expanded its programs’ boundary gradually while noticing that there are a lot of issues in existing tourism industry including local ecosystem destruction, environmental pollution, compulsory shopping that are deeply rooted in package tour program and mass tourism. New travel trend was needed in Korea and Asia region.

However, Travelers’ Map had to struggle against existing tour system and various preconception around tourism in Korea. People aren’t aware of fair travel, even thought tourism industry grows rapidly every year. There also misunderstanding on price and concept of fair travel.

For the last 6 years, Travelers’ Map has been viewed as leading social enterprise in Korea. It was the 1st social enterprise in tourism certified by Ministry of Employment and Labor, and put an effort to change the culture of travelling in Korea and Asia. As time goes by, the number of customers gradually increased from 200 in 2009, 1500 in 2010 to 6400 in 2013. Now, they operate 50 programs in 28 different overseas countries and 100 programs in local areas in Korea except for customized programs for individuals. Moreover, it has contributed hugely to help people recognise the need and importance of fair travel and tourism as well as regenerated continuous preference for fair travel by giving satisfactory experiences in its programs.

Travelers' Map hopes to create unforgettable memory for travellers and produce economic profit to local areas while preserving local environment. The vision of Travelers’ Map is to become the most important fair travel enterprise in Asia, so it vigorously expands it activities and network into Asia by launching branch offices in Nepal and Cambodia.

fields.description:
GIN is a network-based company provider of innovative organic farming solutions for and by underprivileged rural communities.

Thailand’s low-income farmers suffer in poverty-debt cycles due to single-crop chemical farming. Seasonal variations in the weather coupled with inadequate irrigation systems often leave the farmers with poor annual farm yield. This problem is exacerbated by the variations in market prices and devious price quotes from intermediaries who take advantage of the farmers’ lack of knowledge. Individual empowerment, and thus community development, is hindered by low incomes, the lack of access to healthcare and to quality education. Also, without the proper sustainable farming education, farmers  use inappropriate techniques causing environmental degradation, the deterioration of the soils quality, producing CO2 emissions.

GIN tackles these problems by supporting farmers to transform their fields into self-owned sustainable farming enterprises that will secure their livelihoods while preserving the environment.

Long founded in Buriram province in North East Thailand, the GIN has built trust and confidence with the local leaders and farmers. Since its official establishment in May 2008, 1,600 families have joined the network as members, and its customers are already five times the number of its members.  The company is now ready to develop on a larger scale.

fields.mission_statement: To promote forest conservation, preserve local cultures, and improve livelihood of local farmers.
fields.description:
Green Net Social Enterprise operates an organic shade grown coffee business with the mission to promote forest conservation, improve locals' livelihood, and restore traditional way of lives. To fulfil this mission, we engage in the whole coffee value chain, encompassing promoting agroforestry concept, building network of producers, purchasing coffee beans from them at fair price, processing, and distributing the organic coffee products to the market. By generating sustainable income for community forest communities, Green Net SE ensures the long term preservation and restoration of forest areas.

Mono-crop plantation, chemical farming, and forest destruction prevalent in mountainous areas of Northern provinces are causing numerous effects in ecosystem including soil erosion & deterioration, frequent flood, biodiversity loss, and climate change. Furthermore, hill tribes' local ways of life have changed dramatically over the past years; the connection between hill tribes people and nature has largely declined, and the traditional value of locals to nurture environment is also diminished as mono crop culture has entered the areas. Besides environmental degradation and changing culture, local farmers also suffer in poverty cycle due to variation in market prices and exploitative middlemen who underprice agricultural products. Unsustainable agricultural practices, such as single-crop farming relying heavily on chemical inputs and pesticides also exacerbate the problem and put farmers into vicious cycle of debts and poverty, causing numerous problems such as lack of access to quality education and healthcare as well as low community empowerment.

Green Net Social Enterprise therefore encourage community-forest villagers to grow organic shade grown coffee as well as equips them with necessary knowledge & skills in organic shade grown coffee cultivation & processing techniques that preserve and restore forest areas.

Green Net Social Enterprise has been working with networks of community-forest farmers in two Northern provinces, covering 11 villages with 304 producing members and over 9,000 rai of land areas. Their producers’ networks currently produce coffee cherries over 1,000 tons per year.
fields.summary: Promote forest conservation and improve livelihood through coffee business

fields.description:
141 produces wood furniture with a special design of ‘empty space of giving’ to transform the wood residue to creative wood toys for underprivileged children in the effort to promote a better physical and mental growth in young children through Slow Play.

Early childhood, the first five years of life, is a time of rapid cognitive, linguistic, social, emotional and motor development, and the most important period of development in a child’s life when toys play a crucial role in children’s development. Based on Waldorf education, it is believed that toys that are manufactured with full details such as fancy dolls, plastic guns or “finished” toys ties the child to a certain group of activities ; whiles toys that are simply made with less details such as plain wooden car or “unfinished” toys leaves children free to exert their imaginations in a Slow Play culture. Slow Play toys will promote child’s physical growth and health because the materials used are natural and real which will help children to develop a healthy relationship to the material world.

With that philosophy in mind, 141 produce special designed wood furniture which in parallel delivers fine wooden toys for the donation to unprivileged young children in remote nursery care units.

141 is providing over 15,000 pieces per year of educational toys to children in remote nursery care units in Thailand. Currently they are expanding their production capacity through machine and manpower investment.141 plan to set up a workshop to increase the sales channel and facilitate interested parties aiming at families and voluntaries to interact and build a slow play culture in the society.
fields.summary: Provide slow-play toys to children in remote nursery

fields.mission_statement: To develop economically sustainable solutions to energy and environment related challenges
fields.description:
The company was founded in 2010 with focuses on energy and environment.  Currently there are two projects at hand: [1] gasoline-to-gas conversion for public transport vehicles in Cirebon, West Java, and [2] drinking water provision in Papagarang Island, Komodo National Park area, Nusa Tenggara Timur. The company asked for a support from UnLtd Indonesia for the water provision project.  Komodo Island is famous with its amazing natural resources and its komodo dragon. However, due to its dry climate, people around Komodo National Park Area in East Nusa Tenggara faced severe water problem for years. The only available water source is brackish water from local well. Fresh water available only at the nearest port of Labuan Bajo, 2 hour travel by boat, where they have to buy the water. Thus water becomes costly and scarce. In 2011, Komodo WAI was established and together with the community we started to build clean water stations to provide local water supply.

The intake was obtained from brackish water well, which was then purified using reverse osmosis technology, to meet the standard of water safe for drinking. The water was then distributed through gallon size jerry can.

On the first phase, distribution is focused on Papagarang Island, where Komodo WAI water treatment is located. Currently we have served 7 villages in Komodo Islands, covering Papagarang (345 household), Mesa (450), Warloka (325), Komodo (500), Rinca (300), Soknar (80), Lente Golohmori (700), and Kukusan (80). Previously there was an effort from local government to grant a reverse osmosis plant for Rinca, Komodo, and Mesa islands. However, it was lacking the concept of sustainable management. People got water for free, thus resources for maintenance was limited.

Komodo Water apply affordable charges to ensure continuity of the service. We are also flexible with the payment system to accommodate people’s livelihood pattern (People pay after they received income from selling their fish catch of the day). Jerry can was chosen as it was considered the most appropriate for mobilization.

The project has provided affordable drinking water for 2,580 households. It is looking for additional investment to build a new plant to serve 4,000 people in a nearby island, and later on 270,000 people in an adjacent district.
fields.summary: Develop economically sustainable solutions to energy and environment challenges

fields.description:
Orgdot is an ethical fashion oriented social enterprise established in 2009. 6 promising young businessmen from major companies in Korea joined together to start a social enterprise with the aim to change unethical ecosystem of domestic fashion industry.

Fashion industry is major and huge part of the whole economy of Korea, especially in terms of attracting foreign tourists and investment these days. However, fashion industry doesn’t much care about environmental factors even it generates severe environmental pollution through all process of making and consuming clothes. In addition, this industry has become extremely competitive and existing distribution system is distorted. In this system, designers and makers cannot earn money that they deserve to get.

To tackle these problems, it has three type of business now. Firstly, Orgdot designs the natural line of organic cotton, organic bamboo as well as the functional product line of recycled polyester and nylon from plastic bottle or fishing net. Secondly, it focuses on B2B business for government and leading companies, and B2C business with our own casual brand A.F.M targeting young fashion boys in their twenties. The third business aims online platform called ‘Designersnmakers’ connecting fashion designers and sewing factories globally. It is about changing fundamental matter by building a platform to match potential designers and small-sized makers’ factories directly.

As a 6 year-old social enterprise, Orgdot was awarded prizes including ‘Social Venture Competition’ in 2009 by ‘Korea Social Enterprise Promotion Agency’ and also invested by ‘SOPOONG social venture investor in Korea as prominent and successful social venture bringing new culture toward environmental friendly fashion in Korea. It has helped people re-think and change a perspective on how to produce and consume fashion products. The constant business for 6 years expanded customers and clients including big companies such as Samsung Electronics and Google Korea as well as public offices and civic organisations has been expanded, and the revenue has been increased over 1.37 million USD in 2013. Recently the online platform that provides optimal solution for fashion making drags people and investors attention as a change maker of this market in Korea.

Local Alike is a community-based tourism-booking platform that connects hosts from local communities to global travellers.

There are more than 22 million tourists coming to Thailand each year. However, most of the activities are concentrated in few big cities and famous tourism destinations. Cultural tourism spots are developed and presented without genuine care for authenticity and well-being of local communities. Among few community-based tourism spots, the information are not well presented and locals do not have adequate knowledge and training to provide competent services for tourists. Adding to this situation, younger people in local communities are leaving homes and their culture to seek careers in the cities, therefore diminishing the chance for communities to thrive.

Local Alike therefore work with local people in developing and supporting their local homestays, local tour guides, and unique local activities. Its goal is to make sustainable tourism a great experience and beneficial for local people in terms of income generation, economic opportunities, preservation of local cultures and traditions, natural conservation and increased cross-cultural understanding. Our vision is “The meaningful value for tourists and locals alike”. Local Alike is a registered company limited based in Bangkok, Thailand.

Nowadays Local Alike works with 8 communities and counting. Having serviced more than 400 tourists, it is continually expanding tourism venue and the market.

fields.description:
Ork Pi Dern produces films that have high entertainment and marketing capabilities, which will appeal to a larger part of Thai society and broaden the social impact of the film. Ork Pi Dern believes that films are the best medium in which social issues can be communicated to the public and generate widespread impact, as it will raise awareness, create understanding and encourage people to take part in solving the problems within Thai society. In conjunction with each film, the company and partnering social sector organizations, non-profits or corporations will generate social action campaigns for each film and documentary designed to catalyze the discussion on issues raise in the film.

Film as a medium has been found to be very effective at raising awareness and igniting inspiration for the public to take action and do something good for the society. However, the current state of the Thai film industry is focused on the business and entertainment aspects. It industry has overlooked the opportunity to build understanding and to help society in a good direction. Ork Pi Dern aims to create a new generation of people and build a new approach for the film industry which involves pushing for social change for the better through the use of films as a medium.

Being an integrated film house, Ork Pi Dern is specialising in film production, having experiences in working with social organizations by conducting various workshops for youth to use film media to promote their issues to the public, as a form of creating awareness and encouraging people to make a difference. Following that, the organization had felt the need to further develop the social communication tools and focus on driving the youth group who make short films to instead make long films that could more comprehensively express the issue in Thai society, and to reach a broader range of audience with a campaign that can inspire people to create social change.

The first product of the company ‘Love Not Yet’- a film expressing teenage pregnancy among Thai teenager, has successfully launched in August 2011 with a wide interest  among target public viewer and media. With an effort to sustain producing film with social impact, Ork Pi Dern is currently working on the next 2 films.
fields.summary: A social enterprise film company bridging entertainment with social issues

fields.mission_statement: Develop low-cost, efficient, clean and renewable energy with benefit from the use of energy aimed to local farmers
fields.description:
Supreme Renewable Enegery specializes in sub-500KW non-carbon releasing power plants using biomass gasification technology. Aiming at providing energy, economic and environmental independency and sustainable growth for remote rural communities. The company was set up to manage the Supreme Renewable Energy plan (SRE), which is a german -adapted biogasification technology established in Thailand in 2007. This technology gained recognition through the Thailand Energy Award 2010, and the ASEAN Energy Award 2010 for its Community-Based Power Plant initiative.

Many rural communities throughout Thailand are not connected to any electrical system infrastructure. Also, waste disposal is becoming increasingly important with the recognition that landfill is not sustainable and as such costs are increasing. In an agricultural-based country like Thailand, there are abundant waste from agricultural activities which can be recycled.

Supreme Renewable Enegery therefore provide small-scale solution for affordable and secured access to electric power in remote areas, while protecting the environment. The business works by purchasing agricultural waste from local farmers organized in cooperatives, the electric power produced is sold directly to Provincial Electricity Authority (PEA), and then connected to the grid for consumption by the local community. Community Power Holding develops self-owned as well as made-to-order small power plants.

Supreme had already successfully set up a prototype site in Chiang Rai (Northern province)-currently selling electricity to  Provincial Electricity Authority of Thailand (PEA).  Supreme finished the project of 500 kW for customers in June 2012.   Another 2 customers have started to construct the plant and operated since 2013.
fields.summary: Low-cost, efficient, clean and renewable energy from agricultural waste
